    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName ref="pl0002">Chester</placeName> June 1. 1773</dateline>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I give you many thanks for your kind favor &amp; for the verses. I must trouble
                    you get this card answered. <persName ref="pe0199">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Kincaid</persName> who I think is related to <persName ref="pe0166">the Marquiss of Lothian</persName> perhaps will readily do it
                    from <persName ref="pe0594">the marchioness</persName>.</p>
                <p>I wish much also to know who <persName ref="pe0240">Sir Peter Frazier</persName> was
                    whose <rs type="art" ref="ar0114">picture</rs> I saw at <placeName ref="pl0142">Castle Gordon</placeName>, &amp; who <rs type="art" ref="ar0114">
                        <persName ref="pe0029">Sir Alexander Frazier</persName>
                    </rs>, <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0001">
                            <hi rend="underline">Scotch
                            Tour</hi>
                        </title>
                        <biblScope unit="page">p.122</biblScope>
                    </bibl> of what family &amp; what
                    their history.</p>
                <p>I will send <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName>
                    the sheets of <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0050">the
                            Phalainologia</title>
                    </bibl> as fast as they are printed, in franks.</p>
                <p>I find several of <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0064">the Edinburgh
                            Magazines</title>
                    </bibl> missing, some numbers by mistake never having
                    been sent: so after this quarter I beg to have the whole quarter bound &amp;
                    sent to <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName> as opportunity offers. I hope
                    to get the numbers I want, when I have time to name them.</p>
                <p>I am now <del rend="overstrike">
                        <gap reason="illegible" unit="word" quantity="1"/>
                    </del> at <placeName ref="pl0002">Chester</placeName>: &amp; enquire for
                        <persName ref="pe0157">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> M<hi rend="superscript">c</hi>Govans</persName> parcel but it is not yet
                    arrived: which you will please to let him know least he think me negligent in
                    not <sic>acknowleging</sic> the receit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am <lb/>Dear sir <lb/>truely yrs</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Tho.
                    Pennant</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
